comments.body:
[~sjones] I think we need to change line #60 in AuthPreUpgrade420.java from:
{code}
sql.execute(String.format("drop table if exists %s", table));
{code}
to:
{code}
sql.execute(String.format("drop table if exists %s cascade", table));
{code}

[~sjones] Any idea why we may be seeing the following at upgrade?
{code}
Fri Sep 18 05:34:58 2015 ERROR [SystemCredentials:main] [com.eucalyptus.component.auth.SystemCredentials.lookup(SystemCredentials.java):111] com.eucalyptus.component.NoSuchComponentException
: Failed to find credentials for: arn:euca:bootstrap:identity:identity:10.111.1.105/identity/identity identity:unpartitioned:
{code}

[~mmunn1], the failure is due to the database being unavailable, but I'm not sure what the cause is.

You can remove the @GenerateKeys from the Identity component, which would address the first logged error.

There is also an incorrect entity on the CertificateEntityUpgrade420 class, it should be:

{code}
@Upgrades.EntityUpgrade(entities = CertificateEntity.class,  since = Upgrades.Version.v4_2_0, value = Euare.class)
{code}

rather than:

{code}
@Upgrades.EntityUpgrade(entities = Certificate.class,  since = Upgrades.Version.v4_2_0, value = Euare.class)
{code}

but I'm not sure those changes would impact the reported failure.

[~mmunn1], it is safe to change Databases#isVolatile so it will never be true during upgrade:

{code}
  public static Boolean isVolatile( ) {
    return !BootstrapArgs.isUpgradeSystem() && volatileAtomic.get( );
  }
{code}

but it is not expected to be true unless there is a DB connection issue, so this may be hiding an underlying issue.

[~mmunn1], I put the wrong name in VmBootVolumeAttachment#SchemaUpgradeForEntity , it should be:

{code}
uk_muacb67gpe742w0bfxdyk64c5
{code}

not:

{code}
uk_qhck6noa8fca18b72q1hf7vh9
{code}

which was an existing constraint on the volume.

[~mbacchi] I have created a separate bug EUCA-11416 for this latest issue where we are seeing the following in the cloud-error.log. 
{code}
"Failed to upgrade metadata_instances_persistent_volumes"
{code}
This bug EUCA-11386 resolves the error:
{code}
"com.eucalyptus.bootstrap.Databases$DatabaseStateException: Transaction begin failed due to concurrent database synchronization:" issue. 
{code}
And the error:
{code}
Wed Sep 16 13:01:53 2015 ERROR [AuthPreUpgrade420:main] [com.eucalyptus.auth.euare.persist.upgrade.AuthPreUpgrade420.call(AuthPreUpgrade420.java):60] org.postgresql.util.PSQLException: ERROR
: cannot drop table auth_auth because other objects depend on it
  Detail: constraint fk_74wskk1bwox0xh1p1y0e37n4a on table auth_auth_action_list depends on table auth_auth
constraint fk_kgnmdj889fm1032fnyrhi5hor on table auth_auth_resource_list depends on table auth_auth
  Hint: Use DROP ... CASCADE to drop the dependent objects too.
{code}
If you are no longer seeing these in the cloud-error.log you can move this to resolved.
